The paper deals with the problem of word spotting in historical manuscripts using neural networks. This involves image processing (cs.CV), information retrieval (cs.IR), and deep learning (cs.DL). The paper also mentions the use of natural language processing techniques (cs.CL) and the evaluation of the proposed method using various metrics (cs.LG).
